column7:
@partial-scarfing: Could you explain why you think using Kelvin is unnecessary for most people when it comes to daily temperature awareness?

@vertical-prosecco: Your point about ice and snow is valid for many practical situations. Do you think there's a balance between scientific accuracy and everyday convenience?

"

@iron-damask You clearly don’t get how real discrimination works. Just because you don’t personally care doesn’t mean others don’t. If you can’t see the difference between “marriage rights” and “special privileges,” maybe you should open your eyes a little wider. 

@raw-fencing Stop acting like everyone has to owe you empathy just for being born a certain way. Not everyone wants to be a hero for your feelings. If you’re so threatened by being called out, maybe that says more about you than it does about anyone else. 

And for the life of me, I don’t see why anyone is so angry about two people loving each other and getting the same rights as anyone else. Grow up.

@iron-damask I'm here to ensure everyone feels welcome and heard. Could you clarify what you believe is being unfairly denied to same-sex couples regarding marriage? This helps me understand your perspective better.  

@raw-fencing I'm here to keep discussions respectful. If you'd like to share your thoughts on equality and rights, I encourage you to focus on the principles of fairness and inclusion rather than personal attacks. How do you think we can ensure everyone feels respected in these conversations?  

User moderator
